      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_VoucherAllOutstandingBills",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to process manual billing records that have not yet been vouchered. It iterates over billing groups and checks for outstanding bills that meet specific criteria. If such bills are found, it calls another stored procedure to voucher them. Additionally, it updates all manual billing records for the current period to mark them as vouchered, setting specific fields to indicate this status."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves multiple steps, including cursor operations, conditional logic, and updates to the database. While it is not overly complex, the use of cursors and the need to handle multiple conditions and updates elevate its complexity beyond a simple query or update operation."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
